Kosar baji is the wife of M. R., who resides in Borewala, Pakistan, a city famous for its shrines.  Kosar baji is a very hardworking lady who believes people can achieve everything if they work hard. The mother of one daughter and two sons, all enrolled in a local school, Kosar baji pays their school fees by preparing embroidered dresses while her husband runs a medical store in the community.  She is applying for a loan to buy more medicines to increase his profit. <p>
\t
She is the group leader of five other women from her locality:

Naseem baji wants a loan to buy an auto-rickshaw (a local three-wheeled motor vehicle);
Muniran baji and Jamila baji each want a loan to buy seasonal fruits to sell;
Zeenat baji wants a loan to buy leather for her shoe-making business;
Maroofan baji wants a loan to buy fertilizer to sell.<p>

The funds for this group loan will be distributed among the group members, each of whom will invest in her own business. The members guarantee one another's loans so if one member does not repay, the other members are responsible.
